'''Pieter Rossouw de Klerk''' (born 21 August 1989) is a South African [[rugby union]] player for the {{Rut Southern Kings}} in the [[Pro14]]. His regular playing position is [[Prop (rugby union)|tighthead prop]].

De Klerk began his senior career in [[Pretoria]] and made his domestic debut for the {{Rut Blue Bulls}} in 2009 against the {{Rut Griquas}}.   The following year he made his first [[Super Rugby]] appearance for the {{Rut Bulls}} against the {{Rut Highlanders}}.<ref name="Rossouw de Klerk Bulls Player Profile">{{cite web | url=http://www.thebulls.co.za/profile.aspx?pid=698&team=Senior0 | title=Rossouw de Klerk Bulls Player Profile | work=Bulls | accessdate=29 July 2013 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130729105501/http://www.thebulls.co.za/profile.aspx?pid=698&team=Senior0 | archivedate=29 July 2013 | df= }}</ref>   In total he managed 33 matches for the Blue Bulls and 14 games for the Bulls.<ref name="Rossouw de Klerk itsrugby.co.uk Player Statistics">{{cite web | url=http://www.itsrugby.co.uk/player_18460.html | title=Rossouw de Klerk itsrugby.c.uk Player Statistics | work=It's Rugby | accessdate=29 July 2013}}</ref>

He moved west in 2013 and played for the {{Rut Free State Cheetahs}} in the [[Vodacom Cup]] and [[Currie Cup]] competitions.<ref name="Naka lok ’n tweede Blou Bul na Vrystaat">{{cite web | url=http://www.beeld.com/Sport/Rugby/Naka-lok-n-tweede-Blou-Bul-na-Vrystaat-20120813 | title=Naka lok ’n tweede Blou Bul na Vrystaat | work=Beeld | date=13 August 2012 | accessdate=13 August 2012 | language=Afrikaans}}</ref><ref name="SARU Player Profile Rossouw de Klerk">{{SA Rugby Player Profile | id=37376 | name=Rossouw de Klerk | date=4 June 2016}}</ref>

He signed for [[Glasgow Warriors]] in 2014 and won the Pro 12 title in the season 2014-15. On 31 July 2015 Glasgow Warriors announced that De Klerk would be released from his contract due to personal reasons.<ref name="Squad Update">{{cite web | url=http://www.glasgowwarriors.org/news/15/07/31/squad-update | title=Squad Update | work=Glasgow Warriors | date=31 July 2015 | accessdate=30 September 2015}}</ref> On 27 September 2015, Klerk signed for top French club [[FC Grenoble|Grenoble]] in the Top 14 from the 2015–2016 season.<ref name="Grenoble: Le pilier sud-africain Rossouw De Klerk en renfort">{{cite news | url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Rugby/Actualites/Grenoble-le-pilier-sud-africain-rossouw-de-klerk-en-renfort/585237 | title=Grenoble: Le pilier sud-africain Rossouw De Klerk en renfort | work=L'Équipe | date=27 September 2015 | accessdate=30 September 2015 | language=French}}</ref>

